      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To achieve O(n) time complexity, we can use a technique called \"manacher's algorithm\" which is specifically designed for this problem. It's a bit complex, but it's guaranteed to find the longest palindromic substring in O(n) time.\n\nHere's the modified code:\n\n```python\ndef longest_palindrome(s):\n    def manacher(s):\n        T = '#'.join('^{}$'.format(s))\n        n = len(T)\n        P = [0] * n\n        C = R = 0\n        for i in range(1, n-1):\n            P[i] = (R > i) and min(R - i, P[2*C - i])\n            while T[i + 1 + P[i]] == T[i - 1 - P[i]]:\n                P[i] += 1\n            if i + P[i] > R:\n                C, R = i, i + P[i]\n        return [T[i + 1 - P[i]:i + 1] for i in range(n) if P[i] > 1]\n\n    return max(manacher(s), key=len)\n```\nThis code works by first pre-processing the string into a",
